<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,581,894]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517">
Described from the south side of the Groote Swartberg, on the edge of the Little Karoo. New records are all from further west in the Groote Swartberg range, from both northern and southern slopes: 
<date box="[1139,1261,617,642]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2009-09-24">
<number box="[1139,1166,617,642]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="24.0">24</number>
/ix/ 
<number box="[1205,1261,617,642]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</date>
Western Cape, Groote Swartberg, stream on R 
<number box="[503,545,654,678]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="328.0">328</number>
<quantity box="[552,610,653,678]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" unit="km" value="2.0">2 km</quantity>
N of 
<collectingCountry box="[676,709,654,677]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="22" pageNumber="517">De</collectingCountry>
Top, on N side of pass, 
<number box="[985,1047,653,678]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="1700.0">1,700</number>
m—abundant; 
<date box="[1216,1338,653,678]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2009-09-24">
<number box="[1216,1243,653,678]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="24.0">24</number>
/ix/ 
<number box="[1282,1338,653,678]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</date>
Western Cape, Groote Swartberg, Dorpsrivier ca. 
<quantity box="[629,704,689,714]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" unit="km" value="12.0">12 km</quantity>
S of Prince Albert—abundant; 
<date box="[1077,1170,689,714]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2014-01-01">
<number box="[1077,1086,689,714]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="1.0">1</number>
/i/ 
<number box="[1111,1170,689,714]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</date>
Western Cape, Groote Swartberg, permanent stream below Kangoberg on Gamkaskloof road (
<figureCitation box="[982,1053,725,750]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[229,1347,193,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[229,1347,193,1816]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6. Habitats of Mesoceration species in South Africa. A) Western Cape, Matsikammaberg, permanent stream 1 km SE of Sewefontein farm— M. foggoi sp. nov., M. sewefonteinense sp. nov., M. umbrosum; B) Western Cape, False Bay, small stream on R 44 road below Boskloof Peak— M. sinclairi sp. nov., M. brevigranum; C) Western Cape, Groote Swartberg, permanent stream below Kangoberg on Gamkaskloof road— M. barriotum, M. littlekarroo, M. reticulatum, M. splendorum; D) Western Cape, Table Mountain National Park, Table Mountain, stream in Echo Valley— M. abstrictum, M. tabulare. Photos D. T. Bilton." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243048/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="517">
Fig. 
<number box="[1039,1053,725,750]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
C)—abundant; 
<date box="[1241,1334,725,750]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2014-01-01">
<number box="[1241,1250,725,750]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="1.0">1</number>
/i/ 
<number box="[1275,1334,725,750]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</date>
Western Cape, Groote Swartberg, stream on S side of Swartberg pass, below Oliewenberg—abundant; 
<date box="[1242,1335,761,786]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2014-01-02">
<number box="[1242,1255,761,786]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2.0">2</number>
/i/ 
<number box="[1279,1335,761,786]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</date>
Western Cape, Groote Swartberg, first stream on N side of Swartberg Pass—abundant. The aedeagi of all these Swartberg specimens (
<figureCitation box="[283,350,833,858]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1824,1846]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,209,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[181,1405,193,1803]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. Aedeagi of Mesoceration species. A) M. rugulosum sp. nov., holotype; B) M. sewefonteinense sp. nov., holotype; C) M. sinclairi sp. nov., holotype; D) M. littlekarroo, Swartberg, permanent stream below Kangoberg on Gamkaskloof road. Scale bar = 0.25 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243046/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="517">
Fig. 
<number box="[336,350,834,858]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D) have a distal lobe that is more strongly curved in ventral view than that illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" refString="Perkins, P. D. (2008) New species and new collection records of Prosthetopine water beetles from southern Africa (Coleoptera: Hydraenidae). Zootaxa, 1864, 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="2008">
Perkins (
<number box="[158,214,869,894]" pageId="22" pageNumber="517" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
—otherwise they do not differ from the description, and would appear to belong to this species.
</paragraph>
